rComments: Honestly I love him. He's adorable and you can tell how cool he thinks physics is. So many demos. Give him a chance. Love this class!!!
I think I actually fell asleep every lecture. It was a struggle to pay attention.

He's a nice guy, and he tries hard to keep the class interesting with lots of cool demonstrations, but in the end it just feels like you're going through the motions to pass. Tests are not easy, but not hard by any means.

It is hard to rate this class because it was so boring. His overheads were hard to read and he never does real examples (sometimes he will plug in numbers) Two tests and a final (both are open book and open note...which makes it hard to study for) He is such a good guy so if you show your interested/make sure he knows who u are then it will help
Class was kind of a joke, all you had to do on tests was find the right formulas and plug them it.  lectures were pretty confusing although he does try.  Tests are open book so pretty easy.
Lectures were unorganized and only made the material more confusing.
Dry as plain white toast.  Decent class, though, with fair grading.
No Comments

When you are in that lecture hall with him, he takes you on a journey. Although the journey can be bumpy at times, he gets you where you need to go. He adds bits and pieces of his extensive knowledge, relevant or not, into his lectures, and that can be a good thing if you are a physics-junkie like me, or a bad thing if you just want to get it done.
Very difficult to understand. Nice guy, but best saved for upper level physics classes.

Since I had prior experience in Physics, Sliwa's teaching style did not confuse me. However, for a newbie it might be difficult. Sliwa's answer keys for tests are absolutely atrocious, hard to read and some mistakes. It's likely that you don't have a choice but to take Phy11 with him, so just suck it up.

Professor Sliwa is clearly a very nice man and probably very good at the research he does. However, he does not know how to teach. He is unclear in class, and the homework and lectures have nothing to do with the actual tests. If you can avoid taking his class, do so, because if you have any hope of doing well you will need to teach yourself.

Prof. Sliwa is passionate about physics and loves to give demonstrations.  His exams are fair and he offers makeups, which are a great option.  He is painfully boring, but the text book is decent and he posts lots of material to enable you to teach yourself.

Sliwa loves physics and tries to explain the course on a conceptual level.  However, he fails to teach the material of the homework or tests.  Clarity is poor, but he wants everyone to do well and is a nice guy.

He is very willing to help students at office hours, and he is seems genuinely concerned with students' understanding of the material. Excellent professor, and it is nice to see someone that is so enthusiastic about his subject!

This is a hard class, but I have never met a professor more willing to help students outside of class than Professor Sliwa- He is so dedicated to helping students understand the material if you seek him out.
Easy class, comes to conclusions in an odd way, but explains it the next class.  Reviews everything from the class before for most of class then crams in everything new in ten minutes. labs are easy.
I liked him a lot, he really knows his stuff.
I liked him a lot, he knows his stuff.
He is a very fair professor for an introductory science class. Tests are doable and he gives make-ups. Class can be boring, but he is enthusiastic.

Sliwa is a very enthusiastic teacher, sometimes a little too enthusiastic. He writes all over the board, talks fast and speeds through the material but if you need help he will do all that he can to help you. He even tutored me through Phy 12. He knows his stuff and he is very passionate about Physics.

Love him! He's so passionate about physics that it's contagious. He gives make-up exams for the two during the semester. He also gives demonstrations that he gets sooo excited about. He's such a sweetheart. I'll miss him :(
cool

Most underrated teacher.  probably the best one you'll get for an introductory science class/engineering requirement.  Sliwa has a sweet accent from what country I cannot fathom, heavily curves final grades, and has cool class demonstrations (if you choose to attend class).  does unnecessary proofs.
No Comments

I didn't like Sliwa at first, but now that I have him as a recitiation teacher, I realize he's really quite good.. he REALLY knows his stuff, which counts for a lot, he's really nice, and willing to help.. not his fault that phys 11 is a crap course
nice funny guy, not a bad professor
Expects us to understand his ramblings and chicken scratch.  Assigns extra work AFTER the class is over, a weekend before the final because he didn't plan well enough!
No Comments
No Comments
No Comments
No Comments
His accent melts girls like butter!

He's been teaching this class for 35+ years so there are no mistakes in the textbook and lab packet (which he wrote). There are no mistakes. Tests are hard but curved so don't worry too much. He's not super clear and easy to follow in lecture, but work through stuff on your own and you'll come out knowing your stuff. He's a really great guy.

I actually thought Oliver was a pretty good professor, used a lot of effort to know each student's name, encouraged students to give tips on how to make class/recitation more efficient. Methodical at teaching the material, reminds of us relationship b/w new and old material, always guides students along instead of lecturing nonstop.

Terrible teacher, mumbles, doesnt speak, and when we asked him to put a microphone he put it on his collar and he still doesnt talk in it, except when he turns to the board to write something and you shriek in pain because all of a sudden you have his voice ampified a billion times.

If you're a physics major, don't take this class. It's not required for your major, you probably won't do well in it, and you have to compete with Engineers who have studied this material before for the grade curve. Test averages were in the 60s.
A great class, not easy, but small setting, and professor is always there for extra help, and very interesting materials. Fun lab, if you like to build things.

After I stopped attending this class, my grade went up significantly. He doesn't cover nearly enough in class. I suggest teaching yourself from the book, which is mediocre as well, but understandable.
No Comments

Awesome professor! Both classes had two papers and weekly ungraded reading summaries. Lots of class discussion and he fielded all questions thoughtfully. His lectures are entertaining and thorough. Highly recommend.
One of the best professors ever.  Definitely the clearest and most entertaining in the Philosophy Dept.  Don't miss him!
Somewhat dorky but a fun guy, very original thinker, opinionated but friendly and open to student thoughts. Teaches difficult material.

I took Biophysics with her last semester and it was probably my favorite class the entire year. A lot of what we learned was simplified versions of real phenomena, but you still got a lot out of it. She always took part of a class day to basically go over the hard homework problems. Reading the chapters before doing homework is a must.

Not the most exciting professor.  She goes over what you need to know, but often she is unable to explain things in a different way for people who don't understand the first.  She also isn't always good at understanding students' questions.  She's kind enough, though, has a sense of humor, and prepares you well enough for the tests.

Ohhhh Cebe. Sometimes ya just gotta laugh, she's pretty odd, and her lectures aren't particularly compelling. It really helped that I had taken Physics as an AP. The tests are straightforward and doable with some studying, she gives study guides that prepare you well. Just a pretty dry introductory class. That's the way it goes.

She is definitely very helpful. I went to ask her questions every week (even twice sometimes) and she never complained about it. Whenever you have a question, she is very willing to help you. But this is a fast paced course. So you should keep track of what she has done before it is too late.

She is a fair teacher. I would recommend reading the textbook before class because she moves fast. I had limiting physics before this class so it was hard but if you spend time trying to understand the concepts and applying them you'll be fine

I was not strong in physics before I took this class, so I struggled a lot and Cebe didn't help what so ever. Her lectures were scattered, she messed up proofs during lecture, and was useless when I met with her one on one. Scared my physics experience

An intro class of 200 students is not the ideal situation for learning, but Professor Cebe did her best. She has clear lecture notes, if you sit in the first couple row and force yourself to pay attention. She easily gets thrown off by other perspectives on thought questions. Tests are hard, but not impossible if you do lots of extra book problems.

I used to have a strong interest in physics before taking this class. Cebe does not care what grade you get as long as you pass. Don't expect a scale. She spends way too much time on obscure stuff than fundamentals. She makes her tests out of 40 points and takes off 3-4 points for calculator errors- clearly doesnt want us to do well at all.

Cebe is a professor who loves her field of study and definitely cares about her students' progress. I had trouble following her lectures though. She tended to gloss over basic or fundamental concepts and spend too much time on complicated integrals for an intro course. Overall, I found her to be a good teacher.
It was hard for her to connect with students who had never been exposed to physics before.

Cebe is a great professor and Optics is one of the best classes I've taken at Tufts.  If you've seen waves/fourier series before the class is a blast.  If you haven't it will be very challenging but totally worth it.  Cebe loves to help you outside class and  is incredibly charismatic about optics!
Professor Cebe truly cares about the well being of her students.  However, she teaches just a small portion of the material required to take an exam.  Personally, I truly disliked the class.
Very straightforward lectures, pretty intense with the math, very challenging class.  She definitely is helpful outside of class, very nice.

Cebe's teaching is semi-clear and uninspiring.  Also, she teaches straight from the math, and expects you to figure out most of the conceptual stuff on your own.  Careful about asking questions- if it's not a "good" one, she might bite.  But talk to her after class and she's very willing to help!

Cebe is the best! she says funny things, but i don't think she realizes it. also, she's hot.  but really, the class is pretty tough especially if you didn't have much physics in high school.  but i feel pretty confident that i'll be ready for physics 12 now.
Cebe's awesome.  She's got a sense of humor, and she cares about her students.
No Comments

We were given handwritten lecture notes every Tuesday, which the professor read through and let us go. The Thursday classes were student presentations. Problem sets given every other week, which were easy if you plug the information into the formulas from the lecture notes. Professor disappeared halfway through the semester and never came back.

Hands down the most BORING class I've ever taken in my life. Space is such an interesting topic, but he just ruins it completely. Drawls on in a dead monotone without pause. Not interactive at all, doesn't even use a powerpoint or anything. Just talks. Fell asleep almost every class, eventhough I was sitting in the first row (he didn't even notice)

Kenny, as i like to call him, is a fantastic lecturer - sometimes i catch myself falling out of my chair this guy is so funny!! Previous class he talked about timing his wife's contractions while she was giving birth so he could than compare them to Solar contractions - what dedication!

Although this class is an easy A you really need to study for it, and there is a lot of stuff to memorize. Attend the lectures and remember everything and you should be good. I just don't understand why he doesn't give out minuses.

Go to class, take notes, try not to fall asleep. The stuff he's talking about is interesting, but his monotone voices puts you to bed. There is no homework in the class whatsoever, just take notes. A midterm and a final of 100 questions each make up your grade so study for 3 days before and you'll be fine.

I took his class in 1976 and nothing  much has changed evidently, except that now he gives out notes to study from.  In my day, we had an option to take the course pass fail and I kicked myself when I got an A.
He's one of the most interesting professors at Tufts. Awesome, quirky guy , very knowledgeable. Easy A if you study the notes he hands out in class.
Class is not necessary, professor is completely full of himself and really should retire from teaching. He enjoys talking to hear himself speak. Knowledgable but doesn't care about his students.

He is one of the most boring people I've ever seen. He isn't addressing anyone in his classes, just himself. The lights are low and the lecture hall is a good place to sleep. Take the class, don't show up to the lectures, go to his review sessions, where he gives you the answers, and cram them. You're almost assured an A.

Boring as hell, but easy. If you put in a bit of effort (and not make the common mistake of slacking entirely), you should do very well. Every once in a while he gets very interesting just talking crap.

Going to class is not mandatory, but I would strongly recommend it. I went to all clases and although not terribly exciting it's super helpful because then you don't need to cram for the two exams (only two grades in the class). Prof. Lang is an expert and he enjoys when students ask questions and show interest.

Gotta love him. Didn't open the textbooks once, went to class a couple times a month. Lights off,  boring subject, MUMBLING PROF... always fell asleep. If you go to the class right before the test where he "reviews" and cram before the multiple choice midterm/final, you will do very well. Very boring, Very easy. Great way to fill science rec.
Not helpful at all when you go to him with questions. Doesn't show an interest in the progress of his students.
He's super super boring. No need to go to class just know the lectures he posts by heart.

Ken Lang is beloved by some - but honestly I've never understood why.  Yes, his anecdotes can be wonderfully weird, but 95% of classes are him dryly reading slides about topics you will have little interest in.  There's a reason the class is about 25% full for most lectures.
He's the least helpful teacher I've ever had. Doesn't care about his students at all. Don't expect him to care when you have a question about the course.

Pretty much the largest waste of time that has ever been scheduled and called a class. All tests/grades are takehome and the assigned textbook is only slightly more useful than my fourteen year old brother using wikipedia and google. Lang tends to write his books based on student research, and its questionable whether his memory is accurate at all

Extremely experienced in astronomy, however lectures are very boring.  No need to read the textbook or frankly attend class, except for the midterm and finals weeks.  A good way to fill the science requirement if not a science major, but I did not look forward to class.

Awesome professor, terrific class for non-science majors to satisfy the NatSci requirement.  Lang isn't terribly engaging, but is very clear.  You don't have to attend lectures, but you do have to study the notes before exams.  Easy A if you do that.

Wanderers of Space is impossible to sit through. Lang is old and only reads his lecture notes--which are online--for the entire class period. This class is pretty easy except for the week before your exams, when you need to cram because you havent paid attention all semester.

He is a quirky guy with a bunch of funny, random stories but I swear, if you could die from boredom, this class would do it.  It is an easy A, however- as long as you study for the tests.  Also, I didn't have to open the textbook once.
i love A's

A fun guy with great stories. He does his best to explain concepts well and it's clear he loves the subj matter. I went to lectures and studied for the 2 exams and received a b+. Not an easy A like everyone says, but still a good lab-less class for a non-science person.

I didn't buy the textbooks and I got an A-. Study from the lecture outlines he hands out, and you will do fine. Lang is nuts and quirky. Good for a science requirement if you don't like sciences too much.

K Lang is my hero. That having been said, his class is your average huge lecture that most students don't attend. If you go to lecture and spend lots of time before the midterm and final, you will do fine. Lang is my reason for attending class as his anecdotes and personal life are so entertaining.
Very nice man and clearly intelligent and educated, but boring boring boring teacher.  I thought astronomy might be interesting, but it certainly wasn't with him.

Very boring class.  I would stay away from this class at all costs.  I took it to fill my science requirement and it was a big mistake.  The tests are not as easy as everyone says they are, and Lang doesn't give any individual attention.  If you have any problems in the class, forget it, he will not help you at all.  I would tell anyone to avoid.

Dullest class ever.  Seems like he'd be a great guy to hang out with on the side, but class is really hard to stay awake in.  Doesn't attempt to engage students at all, the only attraction is that it's really easy and you have to put in very little effort.  Not worth taking for what you pay to go to school here, though.

This man's ridiculous stories and personality are worth taking the class. Lectures are very straight foward and the material is elementary, but semi-abundant. If you study for the two tests you will do great. If you ask a question he will know the answer.  Seriously I impersonate this guy at parties all the time, he is just so ridiculous.
Freakin' awesome.

Oh, what can I say. This guy sounds like a mix between Ben Stein and Darth Vader. His lectures sound like he's giving a dry-eyes commerical.."The surface of Mars is arid and cold..." WHHAAAT? TAKE THE MICROPHONE AWAY FROM YOUR MOUTH, I CAN'T HEAR ANYTHING YOU'RE SAYING!! DO YOU HAVE BRONCHITIS? He does have a hot daughter who I dream of in class.
I enjoy his class very much.  His lectures are well articulated.  Whenever I leave his class my thrist for knowledge about our universe is fufilled.

Prof Lang is honestly the greatest prof ever. He so cute and tells the funniest stories. He makes class very relaxed and really loves astronomy. His immense passion for the subject makes anyone love it...DEFF take this class!!!

It's obvious that he's really passionate about what he teaches- in such a large class, it's hard for students to give him active feedback in class so I think he thinks people are really disinterested, but the reality is that I'm pretty sure almost everyone finds the information interesting and his stories entertaining.
Extremely well versed in his subject. You wonder how he can keep so many random stories and so much information in his brain at one time.
Professor Lang is great - able to combine intelligence (he wrote the book!) with humor, making class not only informative, but also interesting and fun.

Professor Lang brings the material to life.  His anecdotes add spice to Astronomy, and I find the material to actually be very interesting.  If you stay on top of the notes and the lectures and skim over the text, you'll be fine.
prof lang rocks. very easy course, hopefully will be a very easy A.  much more interested in the material than i thought i'd be

A really great class. Professor Lang is very clear about what we need to know, and makes it clear we have to study the concepts, not the numbers. He's a fun professor with great stories and the subject matter is very interesting. Great class!
Prof. Lang is a great professor and it is extrememly helpful that he prints out lecture notes as well as has a website.  He is also very funny and keeps the class interested!
Great professor.  Always has a funny story or comment that makes lecture interesting and worth going to.  Enjoy the fact you get the notes and outlines, few professors are willing to do that.
Prof. Lang is a great guy-- the class definitely wouldnt be interesting if he didn't teach it. He prepares you well, and he really knows what he's talking about.  This Bud's for You, Mr. Lang.

This class is not a challenge but it is very fun.  Lang is a great lecturer and is very entertaining. Going to class is not necessary, but it's pretty fun and then you don'thave to worry too much about reading the book carefully.
He's a very nice and funny man. The class is entertaining and interesting.

Great Class. Professor Lang is so funny and makes the material interesting even if you do not have a specific interest in astronomy. He's a great professor and the class is unintimidating and highly recommended.
hes really entertaining and funny, i want him to be my grandpa, ive been wanting to give him a hug all class. my favorite class - he's so cool!!

either read the book or go to class, exact same material.  He has a website so you really dont need to go.  The only work in the class are a midterm and final.  Lots of cramming, somewhat difficult test
Best part is you don't have to go to class.  Boring material, but his random comments about everything are entertaining.
easy A. don't have to go to class, but taking good notes in calss makes it easier...theres notes, lecture overviews, and even more notes and tutorials on-line...if u want to do well, u can

For some reason, everyone told me this class was so easy and a gauranteed A.  Its not, and Ken Lang blows, his lectures are so boring and the tests are not on the material he says they are on.  DO NOT TAKE

never have to go to class and its boring anyways, have to cram a ton for tests, nice guy, kind of funny but monotone, no work all semester except midterm and final, not as easy as i thought but not that bad either
funny guy, a little crazy but seems genuinely concerned with students...midterm and final are harder than expected. class notes help.

The class was a total waste of time and I never went.  Lang is very funny and goes off on wild tangents.  If I had really wanted to learn something about astronomy, I could have but I had no interest in the subject and he doesn't inspire any.

Prof Lang is really into what he teaches, but spends his lectures bent over his notes mumbling out things he can't always read. I'm pretty sure once he brought the same notes to class twice. The exams suck - lots of cramming, little learning.

You don't have to go to class, but it helps in studying for the exams. The only grades are the midterm and the final, so if you mess up on one, good luck! They require a decent amount of studying. Don't blow them off!
You don't have to go to class,but be prepared to cram for the mid-term and final. Some of his quote "do you kids smoke pot?" "Grades don't matter" "I measured my wife's contractions"
This guy is the man. He's so funny and his class is really easy. You dont have to go to class but it is an entertaining way to spend 75 min or so.

column1: so glad i took his class

rComments: not as easy as everyone thinks.. def knows his stuff.. kinda out there.. his random stories keep the class awake -- sometimes.. he needs to learn how to use a computer.. seems like a decent guy
No Comments
Boring! Never want to go to class, but he hands out note outlines every week. Strange man.
he's not as boring as I thought he'd be, he's actually kind of funny

Professor Lang is my pre-major advisor. He is a big space cadet, but he's friendly when you get to know him. He had my seminar class over to his house and his wife cooked us an awesome dinner. He is really into Eastern religion and has met the Dalai Lama.

So Stupid!
class is not as easy as you think. you dont have to go to class, but you better study from a week before for midterm/final

Honestly, he's satanic. The workload is so outrageous that you won't know which way is up. The fact that he heavily curves final grades is irrelevant. Without a shadow of a doubt the worst Physics Professor at Tufts. You should go out of your way never to take his classes.
He goes very in depth and is extremely challenging. Unnecessarily hard.

Tobin is an amazing teacher - I took AP Physics C in high school so I had taken calc based physics before. Tests were hard but overall Tobin is a great lecturer (lots of in class experiments) and very accessible outside of lecture. His homework was hard but he really encouraged teamwork.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Tobin is an incredible professor, super passionate about teaching intro physics! He makes the course a lot of fun, and really encourages students to work together to figure things out. He's always happy to help with questions too. Would highly recommend.

physics 11 with prof tobin was both the hardest class I have ever taken and my favorite class I have taken here so far. He is so caring, funny, and interactive with his lectures and makes sure that you thoroughly understand the material. He is also super great outside of class. Because of him, I have learned more physics than I thought possible

Very tough class but worth it if you work hard. Many people needed to drop and the types of problems that Tobin asks of you on homework sets are very difficult. Tobin really cares about the course, which is obvious during lectures, which makes the class doable if you are willing to work very hard.

Tobin is a nice guy and he's very passionate about what he does, but only basic concepts were discussed in class, not really how to actually solve problems. This class (physics 11) definitely takes a lot of time, and having prior physics experience is extremely beneficial. There was a recommended textbook, but I did not find it helpful.

Prof Tobin has been my advisor for two years. To say the least, my confidence and professional potential would not be where it its without him. Tobin cares deeply about his students and never fails to reward a deserving effort. I strongly recommend him as an instructor, advisor, and above just a great and wonderful person to get to know.

Professor Tobin is by far one of the smartest teachers I've ever had. He gives you a lot of resources for you to use to help pass the class. With that being said, the class is still incredibly fast paced, the amount of homework is overwhelming and the tests are extremely hard. It is a hard class even you've had a lot of math and physics experience.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Professor Tobin made the class much harder than it needed to be. If you answer a question wrong in class he makes you look stupid in front of everybody. His tests and homework are incredibly hard since he doesn't go into much detail during the lectures. Unless you've taken calculus based physics before it will be a horrific experience.
Tobin is a really nice guy but the class was terrible. He made it way harder than it had to be and you have to put in an incredible amount of work, and even then an A is nearly impossible.
Lectures were terrible. Problem sets were terrible. Labs were terrible. Clicker questions were terrible. Tests were terrible. Overall: terrible.
Hardest class at Tufts University.
Great lecturer, Phys 11 tests are really hard
The homework is often difficult and lengthy but it prepares you for the difficult tests he gives.

The lectures are great and he explains the concepts very well. Attendance counts for the final grade. Homework is hard, but you are encouraged to work in groups. Take some time to prepare for the exams, they are hard.
The homework is graded harshly (points are taken off even if you have the correct answer). Just make sure you explain even the obvious things in your homework explanations.

Homework is difficult, labs are irrelevant, but the lectures really help you understand the material. On the exams, make sure you explain EVERYTHING you do. In general Tobin is a kind, fun professor and he cares a lot about the way you learn physics.

Tobin is clear in his lectures, and provides a lot of support to help you learn the material. He gives lots of homework problems and and online checkins.  His tests are pretty difficult, and the labs absolutely suck.

For physics 11, you can't do better than Professor Tobin. His method of teaching made me learn real physics, rather than simply the regurgitation of formulas that people often associate with the subject. Although I am not the biggest fan of physics, I really appreciated this class and his enthusiasm for the subject.
He's eh. Loves his clicker questions.
Going to class is a must. The homework assignments were difficult and did not represent questions on exams. Labs are not difficult, but exams were hell.

This class is very difficult. The labs, homework and participation is pretty easy, but the midterms and finals are really hard. You have to spend a lot of time on this class and even then you'll probably get a B.
He wasn't great and doesn't teach in class. My experience was horrible and the final was impossible
Not a great teacher, doesn't help you at all, tests are hard, and he doesn't answer emails.

He's the head of the physics department and he's teaching an intro-level class, so you know he truly cares about teaching. The class is pretty tough, but the truly valuable thing you learn is how to approach solving a problem with various forms of thinking. The most disappointing part of the class was the lab section, which was not very helpful.
Hard and difficult but if you put the time into it it will pay off!  don't be scared by bad grades the curve at the end is very nice
He really cared a lot about the subject, even though it was a low level course. He was my best teacher this year. Fantastic class!
Really funny guy. Knows how to teach physics and make it interesting. Awesome demos.
he was mean in person.  if you don't try to talk to him, you'll enjoy the class.  he can be funny of you don't mind him as a person.

tobin is a smart guy, but doesnt have control over large lectures.  he wastes a lot of time with class polls and can get carried away answering a question that is not related to what is being taught.  overall though, if the class is not crazy, tobin is a great teacher.
the dude is real cool and knows how to teach conceptually hard topics. he is the best physics teacher alive at this moment im pretty sure
He is the smartest science teacher that I have ever had. He puts a tooon of effort into what he does. His tests are fairly difficult, but his teaching is incredible
Guy is a dork but knows that he is and that makes him awesome. He knows his stuff and like he has said, could explain most things to a three year old.
Great teacher, funny guy!! may not seem to be at first, though, since class starts easy, but becomes more and more intensive after a while!!!

Best teacher I've had.  Emphasizes conceptual understanding rather than throwing equations out there.  Clear and easy to follow his lectures and he knows his stuff.  Also likes the use of objects and experiment set ups during lectures which is awesome.
Most intelligent teacher I have ever had.

He rambles a lot, and can be boring. He's a little wacky, but definitely loves the subject. The class he teaches is more about a conceptual understanding than a mathematical one. He grades pretty easy, labs and homework are basically a given 00%. Tests not so much, but he lets you have a cheat sheet for every one.
I hate physics, but during recitation sections, he makes Physics bearable due to the unbelievable love he shows for the subject.

Not good. Doesn't talk about the material in a meaningful way, and doesn't explain anything or talk about how to do problems. He just blabs about nothing.  And he assigned a textbook that isn't published yet, so it's in a binder, but his friend wrote it, so we're basically proofing it, which is a waste of time, since it's not a good book.

Worst teacher ever. He shows up about 15 minutes late everyday, not that it matters, because the time that he is there is spent writing illegible nonsense on the board, often unproved equations, then playing with them and arriving at a new equation, which isn't the right answer, cuz there is no answer, he was just playing with it for no reason!

One of my favorite classes.We did the math & discussed the philosophy.He brings his excitement to the material...sometimes that takes him on a tangent.Very nice guy,shows concern for students. His lectures aren't as structured as some,they are more like discussions...but some learn better that way.
RUN don't walk away from this man's courses. He never teaches the material, is dreadfully boring and is a hard marker in the end. He should not be teaching anymore.
He is such a nice guy, just too smart for his own good :(.
He digresses a lot and can't explain things in a concise matter.  The subject matter isn't that difficult but his lectures make it confusing.  He is very nice and easy to talk to though.
A horrible teacher.

Worst Professor at Tufts. He is unclear, frequently makes mistakes during class, and shows absolutely no interest in the success of his students. He has no business teaching at institution like Tufts.

Prof Guertin gets a really bad rap.  For students who are motivated and work hard, he shows a great deal of concern regarding their progress, and is genuinely happy when his students do well. His problem sets are indicative of his exam problems and you will do well if you make the effort.

Worst instructor that I had while at Tufts. Lectures are incomprehensible and he is often confused, unprepared or distracted. He spends way more time adding noises and flying shapes to his PowerPoint presentations than he does teaching. Take Physics 11 instead.

He is a horrible professor.  He has no idea how to teach physics, he doesnt not really know the subject himself. She is really crazy/wacky. Very unclear and unhelpful, at times confusing students more on grammar points. Assigns uninteresting material. Seems to have chosen favorites within first week of class
She's really nice and and amazing person to have as a professor or just to know.
Nice and fair.

I really enjoyed the topic covered in this class ("The Belle Epoque") so the material we covered was very interesting to me. She chooses to teach from a wide range of resources: textbooks, novels, poems, etc. which provided a good amount of variety and was never really monotonous. Only one test and a project at the end.
Very unpleasant lady, ride and even bad.
Pretty good prof, knows what she's talking about but can be a little impatient at times
It was very interesting, however it quickly became a litature course.
excellent prof, very concerned that her students understand the material, very helpful
very nice, clear

He is very knowledgable and you will learn a lot in his course. Make sure to go to his office hours because he gives great feedback on the assignments, which will then guarantee you do well in the class.

Paul Joseph is really knowledgable but the lectures for this class were really boring. Interesting course material but boring classes and long readings.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: This was probably the most vague class I've ever taken. Interesting subject material, but lectures were incredibly boring. Four assignments for the term - two papers and then another two for the final exam. Very lenient grader and if you're a remotely decent writer it's an easy A.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Professor Joseph is a wonderful professor and an incredibly  warm and friendly person. He may be a little intimidating at first but he really knows his stuff. The readings are important but remember that there won't be any tests, just know the material well enough to write about it. BE SPECIFIC ON YOUR ESSAYS IF YOU WANT ABOVE A B.
Very discussions based class. It's amazing if you're interested in Globalization--because you can relate class discussions to current events and vice versa.

Professor Joseph has made me consider becoming a sociology minor. He is kind, knowledgable, and really makes an effort to help his students understand. I was so impressed by him and this course and I would really recommend it. He has a dry sense of humor that worked for me but I could see it not working for others.

He has his own opinions about the course material and makes them very clear, but he listens and engages with other points of view and is a fair grader. The sociology theories are a little basic and I wouldn't recommend for people who have taken a lot of sociology in the past. Overall, I had a very good time in his class.

Total blowhard liberal, even by Tufts standards.  Thinks he's open minded, but makes sweeping assumptions about people. I don't know how someone could dedicate their life to studying war and have no concept of the subject.  You'll do fine if you agree with him on everything.

This class is what you make it. If you stay on top of readings, attend class and pay attention and partake in discussions, then it's a great class. Interesting material. Professor Joseph is clear, TA was also helpful. Midterms took a while to grade, but were returned with thoughtful comments, and was obvious that care was taken in grading.

One of the few classes I have looked forward to attending. Each class has productive discussion, and one can really learn a lot from the material taught. If you work hard, you will do well, and attending class will allow you to stay on top of your work.
extremely under-prepared for lectures. unaware of the political incorrectness of his statements. unhelpful inside and outside the classroom.
Far and away the worst professor I've had at Tufts. He is boring, uninterested in his own lectures, unhelpful, bigoted and narcissistic. Really should be fired.

The man is very knowledgeable and likes what he teaches. However, he wasn't the clearest at explaining some of the theory. Fortunately, the TA for the mandatory recitation was terrific at clarifying. Grading was based solely on a couple research papers and attendance/participation in recitation, and the papers weren't difficult. Fair grader overall

Globalization and Social Change --- it is a very abstract and complex course. The readings and ideas are all theoretical, and are more geared for an advanced student in Sociology. However, the only graded assignments, 3 essays, are very manageable.

I was initially very interested in his globalization class, but Prof. Joseph's lectures were SO chaotic and boring. I hardly learned anything from them, the recitations were more helpful for sure. Nonetheless, I sticked with this class because it fulfills an IR requirement and the teacher is a relatively easy grader.

Prof. Joseph is a pretty decent professor. He is very interested in the material, but sometimes lets his lectures wander. The readings are very interesting though and if you are interested in the material you will nonetheless love the class. Prof is also very accessible and I recommend visiting his office  simply to have interesting conversations.
nice guy, definitely has TONS of interest in what he teaches, but he makes it kind of easy to space out in class,
Painfully boring.  Would not recommend taking a course with him.

Prof. Joseph was definitely a great professor who has a lot of enthusiasm for this course. There were a lot of readings that you had to be familiar with in order to write the papers well. He was very friendly and brought in donuts occasionally. There is also a community service project involved in the course. Overall, definitely take his class

very knowledgeable professor. really interesting material - although lectures got a little boring once in a while. 2 take home finals which were 2 6 page essay (you had a choice of which topics to do). You need to include the readings in your final to get a good grade - but its not that hard. i loved the class. no txtbk - med amts of other reading.
Lectures got boring but nice guy.
He is a really great professor.  The class is excellent and you will learn a lot.
Great prof!  Very friendly and interesting, especially if you approach him after class.  Put a little effort into your assignments, and you'll do fine.

He's really helpful if you make the effort and express interest in what he's interested in, otherwise he can come off as cold. He like sociologyu of war, so talk to him about that and he'll be more than down to help you out. I do think he favors girls...
soo boring! doesnt make any effort at all w/ his students.. definitely has his favorites =(

boring guy, not very helpful, didnt care about his students, obviously had favorites...many people like him..i however am not one of them

He's Awesome!!!

Professor Tano is incredible. She is a master of the material AND can always clearly explain what you don't understand. She is engaging and really funny in class, really gives you a holistic feel for the Spanish language. Her comments are super specific and she will go out of her way to meet with you and ensure your questions are answered. So kind.
I cannot find the words to describe her. I would take every single of my classes with her if I could. She's easily the best professor I had at Tufts.

Professor Tano is by far the best professor I have had at Tufts. She cares about her students and takes the time to make sure every student feels comfortable before moving on. Nothing but good things to say about her.
Cheryl is the best professor I have ever had even though I have never had her class. Just by reading these reviews, I can tell that she is a real gem. A keeper.
Well organized and makes the material easy to understand. As long as you participate and put in some effort, its easy to do well.

When Mrs. Tano subbed in for Mrs. Oppenheim it was day and night. Mrs. Oppenheim was a teacher trying to push us through the material at light speed whereas Mrs. Tano was a caring teacher who made sure that we understood the material before moving on.

Prof Tano is an amazing professor,  always there for her students; if she can she will help them. Although I don't think she is a native Spanish speaker, she speaks as one. She is interesting and engaging, and if you do your work and put some effort in the class, you will most likely get an A in the class. Definitely recommended!
Taking her again for Spanish 2. The best
She's a wonderful human being and a one of a kind professor who is passionate about what she teaches

Señora Tano is the BEST! She has a great sense of humor and is such an amazing teacher. She does a lot of speaking activities in class, which is very different from high school Spanish courses. She's good at breaking down concepts that English speakers aren't familiar with, and she makes connections to French too! I love her class!

Tano is amazing! She knows her students well and is great at getting students to learn spanish. Format of the class was textbook exercises read aloud, as well as vocab and grammar review from the textbook. Tano and this format make learning spanish pretty easy and enjoyable. She cares so much and is very understanding about late assignments, etc.
FANTASTIC! She is so kind and helpful and she makes jokes in Spanish that everyone can understand. She has to be one of the best professors at Tufts!

Tano is the best!! She is so enthusiastic about her subject, and loves her students. Someone asked her in class once what her dream job was, and she said "I have my dream job." Her dream job is teaching, and it shows!! Get her at all costs, she's amazing. Btw, it's worth coming to class just to see what shoes she's wearing; different every day :)
Really helped me speak spanish better!
Great teacher!! She is really clear and explains things well, and truly cares if you understand or not. She's also funny and a really great person!
Awesome teacher. She's really cool and extremely helpful. I highly recommend her for spanish 2. She's the nicest teacher at Tufts

She is the best teacher in Tufts.  She is funny, smart, kind, and understanding.  She is a tough grader, but she is such a good teacher that it is hard to do badly.  You have to take spanish with her or you are missing out on a lot.
She is the best teacher in tufts.

Tano is great! She's funny and helpful and class is always interesting. She connects well with her students! You will enjoy her colorful variety of outfits! As long as you pay attention in class, tests and papers aren't hard. She reallys helps you speak Spanish better!
Great teacher.  Very understanding, helps you learn, and makes class enjoyable.

tano is a terrific professor.  the class is overall very easy. tano's greatest strength is her ability to understand that her students arent very good at spanish, and act accordingly by never getting annoyed.  she knows how to laugh and have a good time in class.  her assignments are very do-able and easy.  take spanish with her if you can!

She is the best spanish teacher i have ever had, explains things simply and easily.  Great personality and disposition, she makes class and learning a foreing language less stressful and daunting than it is.  GET HER if you are taking spanish!
SO nice! SO encouraging! I learned so much in one semester... and it really was enjoyable! It's not a terribly easy class... but if You put in the time, You'll do fine!
So encouraging and helpful.  Made me want to take Spanish forever--but only with her.
So nice, so fun, and very helpful
Amazing teacher...teaches in so many ways and you learn so  much.  you have to work but you dont mind because shes so nice.  take her if you can!
Wonderful! Not a lot of work, yet you learn so much - also, one of the nicest people you'll meet!
Amazing and fun.  We joke around all class, yet we learn so much.  She helps you learn in different ways.  If you can take her, do!

Awesome!!!!

Solid professor, I think my French improved. Can be a bit boring and there's sometimes tedious homework.

Madame Thomas could do a little more explaining for assignments, and classes are quite boring. Not terrible, but not fun.

Very good professor.  Although much of the class was review for me, it really solidified the concepts we went over.  The tests were fair and justly evaluated.  The work was not excessive for a language class.

Viola Thomas is a very sweet, helpful woman. I did not learn much of anything new in her class, but it was a good chance to practice my French and read a few good books. The worst French class that I have ever taken. Asks yes/no questions - not discussion questions. Rarely discussed the texts read. Instead, questions focus on plot. We spent a LOT of time on grammar, which was totally useless, and watching pointless short videos. She's not a native French speaker, and spoke English during class. Not a 22 level class

Very sweet and understanding professor.  Class had a very loose structure so she was always up for random discussions about the news or french culture.  Very easy going about assignments, barely ever collects them.  Overall a fairly good class.

As far as french teachers go, I'd say Viola was typical.  Weird class exercises, off-topic french culture discussions, etc.  However, I thought she was very nice and easy considering my grade was not much affected after skipping 2 consecutive weeks.

I thought Professor Thomas was not only very nice, but helpful and easy to understand as well. I found this class relatively easy even though my french background was rather shaky. I recommend taking French classes with her.

I completely agree with the person from 6/14/03, they totally hit the nail on the head. By far the worst french class i have ever taken. Given the poorness of her teaching she grades remarkably hard, which is absolutely ridiculous!

One of the weakest french teachers I have had, barely spoke french in a 22 class and also emphasized the grammar while barely grazing over the literature or converstation aspect of the class. The essay subjects were lame and had little bearing on the cour

One of the nicest profs, very easy going, recommended.

Absolutely the best professor I have ever had. I took both French I and II with her, and she made me love it. She also knows more about my life than my actual adviser, and has been really inspirational.
shes super sweet, cares and desires to see you grow in french
Wonderful teacher, will work hard to help you. Maybe the nicest person you've met. Won't go easy on you, but will root for you and do anything she can to help.

Professor Rice is a saint. She is extremely encouraging, and her grading is very fair. Prof. Rice is absolutely amazing. A native of France, she brings her enthusiasm, knowledge, care and fun to every class. Very caring and engaging. Love her.

What a wonderful human being, with an incredible gift for inspiring confidence. I didn't know a lick of French before coming to Tufts, and this is the 2nd semester I've had her for a professor. I'm so sad she doesn't teach French 3 or 4, but she said I could still come to her anytime, and I def plan to do so. I am sure that I will become fluent.
Great Professor. Even better person.

There is never a question that goes unanswered or and concept unexplained. She always makes sure to give us plenty of verbal practice, and to go over concepts in a deep and engaging way. I absolutely love Prof Rice. She's an amazing teacher and woman. I often went to office hours and ended up chatting for 45 minutes. She cares about everyone in French and at Tufts in general and is an extremely nice woman.
Prof Rice is amazing. She makes an introductory class to French so interesting, yet the homework and tests are generally manageable. She's not a difficult grader either.

Prof. Rice is a wonderful professor. With language classes, the professor makes the course, and thanks to her the class learned and laughed a lot (she's pretty easy but motivates you to learn). I'd highly recommend her!

Professor Rice is really great. You have lots of work to do but it isn't that hard. She is so nice and willing to help. Also her tests are pretty easy and she grades fairly. Highly recommend her as a teacher.
Professor Rice is awesome. I had her for both FR1 and FR2 and I don't regret it. She taught me more about language than I learned throughout my pre-college years. Wish I could take FR3 with her.

she is seriously my favorite teacher i've had at tufts so far. she is SO nice and helpful, and a fair grader. she encourages participation, but if you show an interest in the class and try you will do well. One of the best french lecturers in the department. She is very engaging with her students, enthusiastic about the material, and is an easy grader. Highly recommended.

expects you to do alot of work but is really easygoing and not strict, always upbeat and nice, grades fairly, doesn't always teach grammar that well, uses alot of good movies for the class, overall good

had her for both italian 1 and 2. shes sweet but definitely not the best in the department. you dont especially feel you are learning much, just sort of cruising slowly through the course. i felt a little underprepared when i got a new professor for italian 3. but shes ok ifyou push yourself. because she wont really push you.

had her for both one and two and loved her, definitely sticks to the book, but that's a good thing for intro italian. pretty lax about deadlines and things like that as long as assignments are eventually turned in. if you need help, definitely go to office hours though

She is the best Spanish teacher I've ever had.  She is challenging but very helpful, I steadily improved as the semester progressed. Professor Weitzman can be a little moody so just watch out for that. Not a bad teacher, but a really hard grader.  Our class average on everything was pretty low compared to every other spanish class I've been in.  She expects perfection and marks you down for anything less.
This was one of the best spanish classes I have ever taken. She truly engages her students.  I look forward to going to each class
Kind. Interacts with you like a real person. Engaging.

Super nice and encouraging!

nicest professor, very helpful, highly recommended!
Mme Trichard is an excellent professor. She tries to get each student engaged and is really helpful and nice. The class is based on discussion of each day's reading, two papers, and two tests.

really enthusiastic and cares about each student, the best french professor i've ever had
great teacher, really enjoyed class

any grammar class is anti-fun, but Trichard-Arany really does a great job with it, she's an excellent professor! Any class you can take with her will greatly improve your language skills, even for one semester!
Great Teacher, makes class lots of fun.

Professor Pollakowski is great and really made this class her own.  She made herself available outside of class and was always there to answer questions for me and clarify her assignments. I have taken 4 classes with her. She is the sweetest woman ever, and truly cares about students' understanding. She is my advisor and genuinely wants to help me. She gives a LOT of handouts in her classes, but they are helpful for exams. She's a fair grader too!

She was really nice and really great about office hours and extra help. She doesn't grade terribly hard and she explains things thoroughly in class. I just found her somewhat boring? She doesn't add a ton of life to the class.

She is a very nice woman, but classes are boring, mostly due to boring material. She goes over readings thoroughly, but almost too much so you don't have to actually think. Overall, decent teacher but not exceptional.

Very sweet lady and very helpful if you go to see her regarding assignments or classwork.  Readings can be challenging - usually because of vocabulary but they are well gone over in class.  Tests need good amount of studying but very manageable.
Really nice lady.  Helpful, and makes mundane crap seem a little more interesting.

Very good professor. Really engaging in class and always willing to help the students.
Prof. Perricone is great! She is one of the best professors at Tufts. She is very passionate about the topic and I really enjoyed her class.

Active style of teaching. Lots of drills for speaking, expects a lot of busy work. Doesn't create a great environment for learning, because she gets angry if her students don't answer right away. Pretty stressful come class time.

Perricone is AWESOME! She is such a fun person and makes the class super enjoyable while you still learn a ton. I learned more italian during one semester with her than i did of 3 years of spanish in high school. Now I'm even considering studying abroad in Italy.. take this class if you can!!!
an awesome teacher. shes kind ofscary at first, but if you come to class prepared youll be fine. shes good and makes you work.
SHE IS AMAZING. take her classes shes the best italian teacher there is at tufts.

She is one of Tufts gems!

isabella is great! take her class!

teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Caring', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Followed her syllabus to the T. I bombed the first test and went to her office hours after and she helped me tremendously. Would strongly recommend her class.

She is the sweetest woman. This was one of my favorite classes freshman year, and I was a student who had never enjoyed a Spanish class before. She truly cares for her students and wants them to do well.

Prof Oppenheim is truly such a wonderful, intelligent, creative, and funny woman! Extremely nice and approachable. Has high expectations.

Adele is one of my favorite professors to date. She is willing to help as much as you want, and is extremely fair with essays and exams. I had an 8:30 AM class with her and it was one of my favorite classes of the semester simply because she is so funny and awesome!

Very Nice teacher. Willing to help. If you study and go to class you will do well.
Prof. Oppenheim is a great professor, very helpful and makes the subject interesting. I wish she was teaching higher levels so I could have her again.
Prof. Oppenheim is extremely helpful and clear in her teaching. She is accommodating and friendly. I highly recommend taking a class with her, you will want to continue with Spanish.
Always seems stressed which stresses out the class. Instruction not very clear, goes too quickly though really important things like irregular verbs.
sweet, understanding, and a good teacher... she is awesome!

Prof. Oppenheim is great. She's really sweet and definately cares about her students. She's always available outside of class, or to meet after class if you need anything. One of my favorite teachers- I would definately take another class with her.
good prof- funny and caring
She is very helpful, fun, and a motherly person. I'd definitely take spanish again with her.
ALWAYS available outside of class, really cares about her students' progess and is very helpful.  also flexible with due dates & absences.  great spanish teacher.
Great language teacher.  Comes off tough at first, but enjoys teaching and does a great job at it.
very nice very helpful best spanish teacher i have ever had

Pauling is so intense he makes you terrified in class sometimes. However, that teaching style was effective for me and I learned a ton in this class.
